@baseUrl = http://localhost:8096

###
### Random Number API Tests
### Controller: RandomNumberApiController
### Validation: Manual validation - max is required, min defaults to 0
###            Length validation: max 9 characters (digits) for both min and max
###            Numeric validation: min < max
### Response: Returns RandomNumberResponse JSON with value, min, max, timestamp
### Error format: JSON {"error": "message"} for validation errors
###

### Random API - Valid min/max
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/random?min=10&max=20
Accept: application/json

### Random API - Default min (min omitted)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/random?max=50
Accept: application/json

### Random API - Missing max (should return 400)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/random
Accept: application/json

### Random API - min greater than max (should return 400)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/random?min=100&max=10
Accept: application/json

### Random API - Max at 9 digits (boundary accepted)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/random?max=999999999
Accept: application/json

### Random API - Max length exceeded (10 digits, should return 400)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/random?max=1000000000
Accept: application/json

### Random API - Max too large (conversion failure or length exceeded, should return 400)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/random?max=1000000000000
Accept: application/json

### Random API - Min negative within allowed length (accepted)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/random?min=-99999999&max=0
Accept: application/json

### Random API - Min negative length exceeded (should return 400)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/random?min=-1000000000&max=0
Accept: application/json
